subSection.paragraph:
Mysids (also known as opossum shrimps) are one of the major constituents of zooplankton, occupying a wide variety of aquatic environments and playing an important role in these ecosystems. Their role in the food chain has been well documented as consumers of phytoplankton, zooplankton, and detritus (
Zagursky & Feller 1985
; 

Viherluoto 
et al
. 2000

). In turn, they serve as preys of many marine animals, particularly fishes (
Mauchline 1982
; 
Lasiak & McLachlan 1987
; 

Mees 
et al
. 1994

; 
Moffat 1996
; 

Nakane 
et al
. 2011

).

A restricted synonymy is provided including original description, junior synonyms, contributions with illustrations, and references including taxonomic or biogeographic data for the eastern Pacific post-1957 (i.e., after 
Gordan 1957
).

Abbreviations are: St., sampling station; M, male; F, female; OF, ovigerous female; CL, carapace postorbital length; BS, benthic sledge; AD, Agassiz dredge; 
MN
, micro-nekton net.

